Description: liimnotliim – An interview on iHeartRadio notes that Liim Lasalle made a name with tracks like “Pupils” and “Regista Gyal” and that his 2024 single “Eye Sore” further solidified his place in the New York music sceneiheart.com. Those are hip‑hop/rap songs, so he’s a rapper and recording artist.

ezzanaaa – An Instalker profile lists “Ezana @ElvtdEz” with the descriptor “III XL – Mgmt // Curator”instalker.org, indicating that he works in management and curatorial roles at III XL Studio. That makes him a music curator and manager.

Category: Music curator & DJ; founder of That Good Sh*t
Description: annabelleklinee – pirate.com describes Annabelle Kline as a “curator, creator, and DJ” who founded the That Good Sh*t platformpirate.com. Five Cent Sound adds that she started the platform after success with viral playlists and now runs events and artist interviews5centsound.com. She is therefore a DJ and music curator.

khufunajee – In a PAPER magazine feature, creative director Khufu Najee is credited with directing the video for Evann McIntosh’s song “JENN!FER AN!STON,” showing his role as a filmmaker and creative directorpapermag.com.
ovrkast – Ovrkast (Silas Wilson) is described on Wikipedia as an American rapper and record producer from East Oaklanden.wikipedia.org.

Category: A&R executive; founder/CEO of III XL Studio
Description: sickamore – Hits Daily Double reported that SoundCloud partnered with A&R executive Sickamore to launch III XL Studio and described him as the founder/CEO and a long‑time A&R who helped develop artists like Travis Scott and YG

midasgold – Morian Mikhail’s biography notes that he is a self‑taught Caribbean‑American filmmaker, photographer, and creative directormorianmikhail.co. Canal Projects adds that he runs a production and creative studio and works as a creative brand strategistcanalprojects.org.
glynbrwn – In GQ’s profile of rapper Cash Cobain, Glyn Brown is quoted as Cobain’s managergq.com, confirming his role as a music manager.

kelz2busy – Pulse Music Group’s biography calls Kelz2busy a 24‑year‑old “rising R&B talent from New York” who writes and performs songs influenced by R&B and soulpulserecordings.com; thus he is an R&B singer and songwriter.

thezillions – Resident Advisor states that Zillion is a 23‑year‑old DJ and producer from Atlanta who has been DJing in New York for six yearsra.co. Kiosk Radio adds that he now resides in New York and runs a genre‑blending collectivekioskradio.com.

ontheradarradio – The home page of On The Radar Radio explains that the platform delivers exclusive music and interviews, showcasing underground artists and top celebritiesontheradarradio.com, so it functions as a platform for freestyles, performances and interviews.

sam.t.hadelman – On his personal website, Sam Hadelman describes himself as a “journalist, photographer, [and] radio show host”samhadelman.com and notes that he is editor‑in‑chief of Cut/Break Magazinesamhadelman.com.

betteroffalone.mp3 – Jade Gomez: Music writer and editor who joined People as a digital music writer in 2024. She has over five years of experience covering hip‑hop, alternative and electronic music, previously served as an editor at Paste and PAPER magazines and contributes to Complex. Gomez interned at Rolling Stone and The FADER and studied journalism and contemporary music at The New School.

rgphilip – Ryan Philip: Director of Licensing & Music Partnerships at streaming service Audiomack. According to The Org, he previously worked as a social‑media and A&R intern, was an artist‑development consultant, joined Audiomack in 2020 as an associate and later became a board member of DLC Inc. He studied sociology at UCLA and completed a graduate course in music‑industry data analytics at Berklee.

_ot – Otmara Marrero (“OT”): Cuban‑American actress who moved to Hollywood in 2015 and quickly landed the lead role of Izzy Morales in the TV series StartUp. She has also appeared in films such as Clementine and is connected to a New York Undercover reboot.
la.uzza – Lauzza: British director known for directing numerous music videos. The Promonews profile lists a long catalogue of video credits, confirming him as a prolific music‑video director.

squarebiz – Maurice Slade: Co‑founder of the southern‑themed party series Grits & Biscuits. A Grio article explains that brothers Maurice and Alzo Slade and Erika Lewis launched the parties in 2010 and have since built them into a popular southern hip‑hop event series across U.S. cities.

igweaka – Igwe Aka (Anthony Aka): Nigerian‑born rapper who grew up in Sacramento. His official biography notes that he began rapping at a young age, co‑founded a brand with producer Ugo, released demos such as Blackness and Lime Green Lounge and the mixtape The Classics Vol. 1, and performs under the name Igwe Aka.

taiyegodbody – Taiye Godbody: Conceptual and documentary photographer who grew up across multiple cultures. His about page states that he uses photography to connect global communities, has exhibited work in New York, Germany and Ivory Coast, has been featured in ESSENCE and The Washington Post, and is represented by Flink Artists.

rickybravo__ – Ricky Bravo: DIY hip‑hop rapper and producer from East New York and Atlanta. Hashtag Magazine notes that he self‑recorded and engineered his album Telegram Titan, began making beats at 14, produced for artists like Icewear Vezzo, Lil Zay Osama and Don Q, and pairs bouncy production with introspective lyrics.

daraibym – Dara McIntosh: President of The Blueprint Group. The company biography describes her as the operations manager and gatekeeper to the firm’s executives, overseeing staff across offices and supporting high‑profile artists such as Lil Wayne, Nicki Minaj and G‑Eazy.

maryjaynee___ – Mary Jayne (Jane Rojanavilaivudh): DJ and member of Jetlag, an event‑planning group run by NYU Music Business students. A Washington Square News article reports that Jetlag hosts parties at venues like RadioNublu and Mary Jayne performs DJ sets, bringing infectious energy to the late‑night crowd.

armin.motamedi – Armin Motamedi: Artist‑and‑repertoire manager at SoundCloud and founder of the management company Seeing Sounds. A ForTheYouth profile states that he landed an A&R role at SoundCloud and manages artists such as Samara Can, Pyrex Pryce, Kevin Powers, Grange, BALE and AyoWhit, with aspirations of running his own label.

jesskenneymusicgrowth – Jess Kenney: Founder and chief strategist of Jess Kenney Music Growth Consulting, LLC. Her consulting site notes that she has over 15 years of industry experience, built streaming departments at Verve Label Group and SoundCloud’s roster, and led campaigns that propelled artists like Laila! to No. 1 on multiple platforms.
nabilahbalthazarr: This handle appears to be a private or personal account. No credible public biographies or articles were found, so its category and description remain unknown.

themonkeykingnyc – The Monkey King: Southeast‑Asian restaurant and bar in Bushwick, Brooklyn. A tourism article describes it as a vibrant venue serving Thai and Malaysian dishes with colorful décor and innovative cocktails.

whojiggi – WhoJiggi: Producer known for sampling century‑old songs and flipping them into modern beats. Type.Set.Brooklyn articles highlight his work looping the 1921 song “The Sheik of Araby” for Chow Lee and sampling a 1924 operetta for B Jack$, and the Wikipedia page on “Fisherrr” credits him as a co‑producer of the viral track.

leroybenros – Le’Roy Benros: Music industry executive and personal manager. In a Knockturnal interview he is introduced as a vice‑president of A&R and manager behind the duo Lion Babe. He describes getting his start interning at Sony Urban (working on Beyoncé’s B’Day and John Legend’s Get Lifted) and at G.O.O.D. Music and Hustle Management before managing his first client Charles Hamilton.

kieranpressreynolds – Kieran Press‑Reynolds: Writer covering music and internet culture. His website states that he writes a weekly Pitchfork column called “Rabbit Holed,” focusing on internet phenomena, and that he previously made comedic YouTube videos.

vhs_boyz – VHS Boyz: New‑York‑based production company specialising in music videos, event recaps and commercials. The company’s site and co‑founder Dillon Weidler’s LinkedIn profile state that he (also known as Wav3) is part owner and head director/editor of VHS BOYZ LLC, a production company he runs that creates music‑related videos from concept to final edit.

whatnycsoundslike: An Instagram‑based platform that describes itself as New York’s leading outlet for music and rap news, sharing freestyles, performances and updates on emerging artists. No independent articles were found to verify additional details, so this description is based on the account’s own tagline.

powr_trav – PoWR Trav: Up‑and‑coming hip‑hop producer from Long Island. A Croxxings profile notes that he grew up in a single‑mother household, was exposed to music through Michael Jackson and Prince, started uploading beats to YouTube in 2018 (his first beat accrued hundreds of thousands of views), has placements with artists such as Bobby Shmurda, Bandmanrill and Lougotcash, and released his sample‑heavy debut LP PoWR Surge in 2022.

Matthew Ali is a music artist and producer from New Jersey affiliated with MHPG Sound collective and the "Slizzy Movement." His account promotes his music (including track "faceandbody") and artistic visuals, targeting hip-hop/rap music fans interested in emerging New Jersey artists and the underground music scene. Has 5,591 followers and 7.6K monthly Spotify listeners.
This account could not be analyzed as it appears to be private, deleted, or has very limited online presence. No accessible content was found during research.

A fan or promotional account dedicated to supporting artist "prodlaila" with 697 followers. Serves as "the official source for all things @prodlaila," focusing on promoting the artist's music, sharing updates, and building a community around this musician within a niche fanbase.

NRG Visuals, operated by Sonia Broman, is a professional photography and videography business specializing in diverse visual storytelling. Features high-quality photography across multiple genres, queer project content, and has worked with major brands like Nike. Targets potential clients and creative industry professionals seeking inclusive visual content.

Zohran Kwame Mamdani is a New York State Assembly member representing Queens' 36th district and 2025 Democratic NYC mayoral nominee. His account focuses on progressive political content, campaign messaging for policies like rent freezing and universal childcare, and grassroots political organizing targeting NYC voters and progressive activists.

A personal account with creative leanings, featuring 3,115 followers and 82 posts. The account appears to maintain a quality-over-quantity approach with selective sharing and curated content. Targets personal connections and creative peers, though specific creative focus remains unclear from available data.

Barter is a business platform connecting brands with content creators and micro-influencers for product-based collaborations. Facilitates cashless exchanges where brands offer products in return for user-generated content like TikToks and Reels. Targets small to medium businesses seeking cost-effective influencer marketing solutions.

A pop culture and entertainment-focused account covering current cultural trends, entertainment news, celebrity updates, and viral content analysis. Features trending topics, memes, and cultural commentary targeting young adults and millennials interested in staying current with entertainment trends.

Enzo The Magazine is a creative publication and media brand focusing on arts, entertainment, and cultural content. Organizes events like "The Enzo Film Festival" in NYC and creates collaborative creative projects. Features artistic and avant-garde content targeting creative professionals, artists, and individuals interested in independent media and NYC cultural events.

Vontee The Singer is an emerging R&B artist from the Bronx with 21K followers. His account showcases his music career through song promotion (available on Spotify, Apple Music, SoundCloud), music videos, and behind-the-scenes content. Targets R&B and hip-hop fans interested in emerging New York artists, balancing professional music promotion with authentic personal branding.

Tatiana Yan Snead - Pandora Black Music Editor, Reasonable Dialogue host, music industry expert focusing on artist spotlights and industry insights

Maxwell Warren Jardine - 20-year-old New Zealand producer and pioneer of "sigilkore" (trap/hyperpop/electronic fusion). 101K followers with only 24 posts using quality-over-quantity strategy. RIAA Gold certified for "I LOVE YOU HOE" with Odetari, 800+ million cumulative streams. High-profile collaborations with Trippie Redd and Lil Nas X. Based between Auckland and Los Angeles, represents new generation of genre-fluid bedroom producers building global audiences while maintaining artistic authenticity.

Account proved completely untraceable through public web sources, influencer databases, social media analytics platforms, or general online discussions. May indicate private account with minimal public engagement, very new account without external mentions, or deactivated profile. Demonstrates that not all digital creators maintain discoverable online footprints beyond their primary platforms.

Marquise Miller - High-end celebrity fashion stylist based in Los Angeles with 17K followers. Specializes in sustainable luxury vintage curation, styling major clients including Joey Badass, Khalid, and NBA player Anthony Edwards. Unique approach combines LA streetwear with luxury brands, emphasizing sustainability through Millersroom vintage store. Recent work includes Complex Magazine covers and upcoming Walmart collaboration, bridging underground culture with mainstream retail.

Ruslan Mediavilla Solovieva - 26-year-old Spanish producer with 45,402 followers, pioneering avant-garde electronic music with Latin urban influences. Born to Belarusian family, conservatory-trained from age 4, creates "digital melancholia" from Madrid bedroom studio. Warner Records deal, 4 million monthly Spotify listeners, collaborations with C. Tangana and Rosalía. Key figure in Spanish experimental pop's global expansion.

James Blake - Established British electronic/R&B artist with 730K followers and just 68 posts, prioritizing direct fan engagement over social media metrics. Grammy winner openly criticizing Instagram's algorithm limitations, developing alternative platforms like Vault for fan subscriptions. Recent collaborations with Kendrick Lamar, Beyoncé, and upcoming album with Lil Yachty. Independent business model innovations challenging traditional music industry structures.

CART Department - Specialized automotive arts and heritage curator with 4,311 followers. Highly selective content focused on automotive engineering history and technical craftsmanship. Magazine-style approach to automotive education, featuring projects like BMW 7 Series cutaway documentation. Serves dedicated community of engineering enthusiasts and industry professionals, proving expertise-driven content builds authority in specialized markets.

Hyperlocal NYC culture and street content creator operating within ecosystem popularized by Sidetalk NYC. Creates authentic NYC street culture content using local slang and cultural references. Multi-platform presence (Instagram, TikTok, Twitter) with brand consistency while maintaining hyperlocal cultural authenticity. Represents growing trend of location-specific content creators serving as cultural interpreters for their communities.

Saint Hoax - Pseudonymous Syrian digital artist with 2.03 million followers creating "POPlitical art" - satirical socio-political commentary using pop culture iconography. Viral "Happy Never After" campaign featuring Disney princesses addressing domestic violence became Amsterdam's official anti-domestic violence campaign. Blends Middle Eastern perspective with American pop culture literacy while maintaining complete anonymity, enabling global artistic discourse without geographic constraints.

Account completely untraceable through public web sources, similar to @jayzeedub. No presence in influencer databases, social media analytics platforms, or online discussions. Could indicate private account, minimal public engagement, very new account without external mentions, or deactivated profile. Highlights that digital visibility varies dramatically among creators.

router.zip – Router: creative technology studio in Ridgewood, New York. An interview with co‑founder Scott Diekema explains that Router began as an interactive art project in 2020 and evolved into a studio run by Diekema, Sam Lowe and Nicholas Byrne; the studio develops bespoke software and motion‑graphics work for music and brand clients.
ghetto.blues: appears to be an Instagram account promoting GHETTO & BLUES, a hip‑hop/rap album released April 11 2025 by rapper MulaManDam. No independent biography for the account exists.

dicefm – DICE: London‑based ticketing platform and app. DICE’s mission page notes that since 2014 it has aimed to break down barriers in the live‑event industry by providing an app that lets fans discover and buy tickets to gigs, club nights, festivals and other events easily and fairly.

demondrext: appears to be a personal Instagram account describing the user as a talent manager for “Xtrodinary Talent Akademy.” There were no reliable external articles or biographies to verify details, so its category and description remain unknown.

hotirontest: this handle seems to be associated with viral “hot iron test” casting videos on social media. It does not correspond to a documented individual or organization, so no reliable biography is available.
hangpronyc: likely an events community account (perhaps “The Hang NYC”), but there are no independent sources describing it; without verified information its category remains unknown.

beekay.art – Brian Kwon (Bee Kay): Bay‑Area‑born artist, poet and “amateur mythographer.” An exhibition description notes that Kwon draws from illustrative traditions and candid ethnography to create epic, intricate landscapes and aims to expose surreal parallels and symbolic malleability in his work.

bk.warehouse – BK.Warehouse: creative event venue in Bushwick, Brooklyn. Tagvenue’s listing describes it as a 1,300‑sq‑ft industrial space with high ceilings, lounge furniture, sound and DJ decks, suitable for music events, pop‑ups, private parties, art shows and brand activations, complete with bar service and security.

rnr.nyc – RNR Bushwick Dispensary: cannabis dispensary and lounge in Bushwick. The dispensary’s website portrays it as a refined retreat where premium cannabis is offered in a space with curated art, warm lighting and natural touches capturing the neighborhood’s creative spirit.

jmsn – JMSN (Christian Berishaj): Albanian‑American singer‑songwriter, multi‑instrumentalist and producer. A biography from All American Speakers explains that Berishaj, raised in Eastpointe, Michigan, wrote and produced his debut album Priscilla in 2012, directs his own videos, and runs his own White Room Records label.
